							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/patrick-ryan/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-04-at-2.17.41-PM-100x100.png" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-04-at-2.17.41-PM-300x300.png 2x" alt="Patrick Ryan" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/patrick-ryan/">Patrick Ryan</a></h6>
										Patrick Ryan is the author of the novel <em>Buckeye</em>. He is also the author of the story collections <em>The Dream Life of Astronauts</em> (named one of the Best Books of the Year by the<em> St. Louis Times-Dispatch</em>, Lit Hub, Refinery 29, and Electric Literature, and longlisted for The Story Prize) and <em>Send Me</em>. His work has appeared in <em>The Best American Short Stories</em>, the anthology <em>Tales of Two Cities</em>, and elsewhere. The former associate editor of <em>Granta</em>, he is the editor of the literary magazine <em>One Story</em> and lives in New York City.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
							</div>
